@Node "Introduction"

UserTool is an easy, User Interface Style Guide compliant method for adding and removing users and groups under MultiUser File System.

I basically wrote it in response to the MUI application that was written for this purpose because I consider MUI to be interface overkill and in huge violation of the 10th commandment of Amiga programming (and I quote Dianne Hackborn):

Commandment #10: RKMs 3:16 (Libs)  Thou shalt not covet thy neighbour's memory protection, though shalt not covet thy neighbour's virtual memory, nor his resource tracking, nor his RTG, nor his marketing, @{b}nor any thing that will require more than a 68000.@{ub}

I'll also be the first to say bring up that I do require reqtools.library. However, 41k is a much easier addition to any system than 250+k.

@EndNode

